"***Question 1: \"How likely is it that Bond will escape from Le Chiffre?\"***\n1. Not very likely\n\nBond has just been caught off guard and overpowered by Le Chiffre and his gunmen. He has been disarmed and his comb, which might have been used as a makeshift weapon, has been taken away from him. He feels \"puny and impotent\", which suggests that he is in a vulnerable position and unlikely to escape.\n\n***Question 2: \"How suspenseful do you find this passage to be?\"***\n6. Very suspenseful\n\nThe passage is suspenseful because it sets up a tense and unexpected situation for Bond. The reader is left wondering how Bond will escape from Le Chiffre and his men, and the description of Bond's feeling of vulnerability and impotence creates a sense of tension and uncertainty.\n\nQuestion 1: 1\nQuestion 2: 6"